  abstract = {The Australia and Pacific region is home to nearly a quarter of the world’s languages. Wordlists of a few of
these languages date back to the first European explorers, while detailed dictionaries have been prepared
for somewhere less than 5 \% of them. Where an indigenous language is the official language of a country
of this region it is more likely to have a dictionary and ongoing administrative support for lexicographic
